description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IMPERIAL COLLEGE HEALTH CARE NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SURGERY AND CANCER CLINICAL PROGRAM GROUP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Substantive Consultant in Palliative Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6 PA / Less than Full Time &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;R&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ef: 290-CONB508&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an innovative and enthusiastic palliative care consultant to join our palliative care team at Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust. This post is substantive and is based predominantly at Hammersmith Hospital alongside another palliative care consultant. The palliative care team at the Hammersmith has a close working relationship with haematology and renal teams including the dialysis services and we are hoping to recruit a palliative care consultant interested in palliative care in haematology, renal or cardiology. There are opportunities for service development, quality improvement, education and training which can be guided by the interests of the successful applicant. Excellent communication skills and commitment to education are essential. The successful candidate will be part of a telephone based on-call service providing out of-hours advice to the acute hospital services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prospective candidates should be within 6 months of obtaining their CCT, or be listed on the GMC Specialist Register for Palliative Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post has been approved by the Royal College of Physicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 2nd December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PROMOTING EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion or visit please contact Dr Sarah Frearson, Clinical Lead for Palliative Medicine on 0203 311 1402 or sfrearson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
